import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['people'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the trend of population growth over the years?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['age'].hist(bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of age in the population?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['sex'] = data['sex'].replace({1: 'Male', 2: 'Female'})
    sex_data = data.groupby('sex')['people'].sum()
    sex_data.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.title('What is the gender distribution of the population?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y')
    male_data = data[data['sex'] == 1]
    female_data = data[data['sex'] == 2]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax.bar(male_data['age'], male_data['people'], label='Male')
    ax.bar(female_data['age'], female_data['people'], bottom=male_data['people'], label='Female')
    ax.set_xlabel('Age')
    ax.set_ylabel('People')
    ax.set_title('What is the age distribution of males and females in the population?')
    ax.legend()
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    age_groups = data.groupby('age')['people'].sum()
    plt.pie(age_groups, labels=age_groups.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of population across different age groups?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
